product_name: Pennington Cedar Bluebird House
review_title: Hole too big or floor too small
review_text: I like that this is made from cedar and I like that its made in the USA. Unfortunately the size of the hole and the size of the floor of the nesting box mean that its not ideal for any one species of bird. The hole measures 1.5" and the nesting box floor is 4.25 inches by just under 4 inches. For my area birds that would use such a small nesting space would also prefer a smaller hole. And although this is a called a bluebird house, the western blue bird in my area prefers a 5"x5" nesting space, making this too small. Finally, it would be better if it had an extended entrance (like the ones you see with an additional block of wood attached to the hole area) to keep predatory birds from sticking their beaks and heads through.

So every spring I find myself patching several spots. I decided to go with an all in one approach this time. It has been about three weeks and the grass is coming in nicely. It is a little more patchy than I would have likes, but I also did not put any straw down. Overall, I am pretty pleased with the results, I may have to do another pass with the seed, but it already looks so much better than it did at the end of March.
